From: buytaert@imec.be (Steven Buytaert)
Subject: Re: /proc info ?
Date: Thu, 2 Dec 1993 08:56:19 GMT

Mr. Bassman (bassman@isoit034.bbn.hp.com) wrote:
:       Is there a readme or some such similar about /proc ?  I wish to write

 Seems to me that currently not that many people know about the LDP.
 The Linux Documentation Project. I had several replies by mail asking
 what it was and where to get it.

 The LDP currently has currently 5 *ALPHA RELEASES* going. 

 - the Linux kernel hackers guide
 - man pages for system calls
 - the installation and getting started manual
 - the network administrators manual
 - the system administrators manual

 For me these have been already a treasure for finding information. Please,
 don't only read them, evaluate them also and let the authors know what you
 like and don't like, i.o.w. help them getting these manuals become better 
 then any *NIX manual I've ever seen. (thanks Lars, Matt, Michael, Olaf and
 the man pages team...)

 The documents can be downloaded from the "normal Linux ftp sites". Look
 in the alpha directory or in the docs directory for another directory
 called LDP. 

 On sunsite.unc.edu you will find them in the directory
 pub/Linux/docs/linux-doc-project together with the 
 manifesto and README.

 To come back to the /proc question. In the Kernel hackers guide there
 is a *fairly* complete /proc section. I think Michael is awaiting input
 from other wizards to complete the section...

 In hope this has helped a bit...

