From: ccoprfm@prism.gatech.EDU (Monte Freeman)
Subject: HD timeout/reset
Date: 2 Dec 93 04:59:42 GMT

Hello,

 Starting when I upgraded my kernel to 0.99pl12 I began to see these messages:

    HD timeout
    HD-controller reset
and
    Floppy: unexpected interrupt

 The first one happens only during *some* hard drive accesses. I've noticed
that it doesn't seem to matter if it's a read or a write.

 The second one happens at random times. There does not have to be any drive
access (hard or floppy) going on.

 I'm the only one logged into this machine, so it can't be being caused by
another user doing something....

 Let's see, system stats:

   386DX40 Cyrix processor
   8 megs of RAM
   Maxtor 7345 IDE hard drive   (345 Megs)
   Generic IDE/Floppy controller
   Currently running .99pl13r  (Slackware 1.1.0 install code)

 Anyone have any ideas what's causing these messages? The one about the floppy
unexpected interrupt isn't that bothersome. But the HD timeout stuff makes me
a little nervous. I'm afraid that it's going to cause me to lose some data at
some point...

     Suggestions anyone?


